# KinderSpark UI Consistency Guide

This rule standardizes look-and-feel across roles (child, parent, teacher, admin/principal). It applies to React/Next files, and references shared components for quick navigation.

## Global Tokens
- Spacing: xs 4, sm 8, md 12, lg 16, xl 24
- Radius: sm 10, md 16, lg 20, xl 24
- Shadows: sm var(--app-shadow-sm), md var(--app-shadow-md)
- Typography: Title lg 20/24 bold; Subtitle 14/20 semibold; Body 12/18 semibold; Caption 10/14 bold
- Surfaces: card var(--app-surface); soft var(--app-surface-soft); border var(--app-border)

## Buttons (all roles)
- Sizes: sm 28px, md 36px, lg 44px heights
- Label case: Title Case
- Icon gap: 6–8px, icon size 14–18
- Press feedback: app-pressable + active:scale-95
- Primary: gradient or role-accent; Secondary: surface soft; Destructive: red scale

## Cards
- Padding: md (12–16px) internal; Grid gaps consistent
- Border: 1–1.5px var(--app-border); Surface: var(--app-surface) or soft for emphasis
- Rounded: md (16) for standard, lg (20) for hero

## Navigation and Sign Out
- Top bar: no Sign Out button.
- Sign Out lives only in Profile/Settings for every role with same icon and label.
  - Icon: ↯ (or Lucide LogOut) sized 16–18
  - Label: "Sign Out"
  - Confirmation modal; clears tokens; server revoke via logoutApi
  - Same placement block beneath account info
- Affected files to align:
  - [frontend/components/TopBarActions.tsx](mdc:frontend/components/TopBarActions.tsx)
  - [frontend/components/ParentSidebar.tsx](mdc:frontend/components/ParentSidebar.tsx)
  - [frontend/components/DashboardSidebar.tsx](mdc:frontend/components/DashboardSidebar.tsx)
  - [frontend/components/ProfileManager.tsx](mdc:frontend/components/ProfileManager.tsx)

## Profile Header Layout (all roles)
- Avatar left, name + role stacked, action chip row below
- Copy Profile ID component identical across roles
- Location/Weather: show Parent/Teacher only; hide on Child/Admin. If permission denied, show compact "Enable location" chip instead of placeholder.

## Empty/Loading
- Use shared `<Loading />` and `<InlineEmpty />` with same emoji+copy and spacing
- Avoid one-off spinners

## Responsive
- Mobile-first; tablet grid gap 12–16; card max widths consistent

## Locale and Accessibility
- All interactive text through i18n; large tap targets; haptic on critical confirms

## Deployment Freshness
- Service worker should prompt "New version available — Refresh" to avoid stale UI after deploys
